messages.message:
team, I'm trying to publish an app in a crafting sandbox I created, I have a test project, and trying to publish an app. any advice on where to start debugging? I see this as the last response in the network log
```{
    "status": "OK",
    "msg": "",
    "state": "DONE",
    "is_waiting_for_resources": false,
    "job_id": "b789f16a-42fc-4443-922a-1145cc83a56e",
    "results": [
        {
            "status": "ERROR",
            "msg": "Failed to create the app"
        }
    ],
    "cur_status": "{\"msg\": \"Adding to the database\"}",
    "completed_count": 1,
    "finish_timestamp": null,
    "binary_mode": false
}```
tried rebuilding mysql, and the entire sandbox, same error
ok im good now, figuring out how to debug and was able to pull master, rebase, and everything's good now

did you pull master?

we merged a fix for this last week https://github.com/instabase/instabase/pull/71406

ah yes, you needed to rebuild and restart `celery-app-tasks`

so `cs restart celery-app-tasks` should have sufficed
